00:41:09.434 --> 00:41:12.367
[laughter]

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:21.400
Pausch: IT WAS
AN UNUSUAL COURSE

00:41:21.400 --> 00:41:24.167
WITH SOME OF THE MOST BRILLIANT,
CREATIVE STUDENTS

00:41:24.167 --> 00:41:26.701
FROM ALL ACROSS
THE CAMPUS.

00:41:26.701 --> 00:41:29.267
IT JUST WAS A JOY
TO BE INVOLVED.

00:41:29.267 --> 00:41:31.601
AND THEY TOOK THE WHOLE STAGE
PERFORMANCE ASPECT OF THIS

00:41:31.601 --> 00:41:33.133
WAY TOO SERIOUSLY.

00:41:33.133 --> 00:41:36.334
[laughter]

00:41:36.334 --> 00:41:39.234
AND IT BECAME THIS
CAMPUS PHENOMENON EVERY YEAR.

00:41:39.234 --> 00:41:41.400
PEOPLE WOULD LINE UP FOR IT.

00:41:41.400 --> 00:41:43.334
IT WAS VERY FLATTERING,

00:41:43.334 --> 00:41:47.067
AND IT GAVE KIDS
A SENSE OF EXCITEMENT

00:41:47.067 --> 00:41:50.701
OF PUTTING ON A SHOW FOR PEOPLE
WHO WERE THEN EXCITED ABOUT IT,

00:41:50.701 --> 00:41:52.467
AND I THINK THAT THAT'S
ONE OF THE BEST THINGS

00:41:52.467 --> 00:41:53.767
YOU CAN GIVE SOMEBODY,

00:41:53.767 --> 00:41:56.334
THE CHANCE TO SHOW THEM
WHAT IT FEELS LIKE

00:41:56.334 --> 00:41:58.634
TO MAKE OTHER PEOPLE
GET EXCITED AND HAPPY.

00:41:58.634 --> 00:42:00.367
I MEAN,
THAT'S A TREMENDOUS GIFT.

00:42:00.367 --> 00:42:02.234
WE ALWAYS TRIED
TO INVOLVE THE AUDIENCE,

00:42:02.234 --> 00:42:03.767
WHETHER IT WAS PEOPLE
WITH GLOW STICKS

00:42:03.767 --> 00:42:07.133
OR BATTING A BEACH BALL AROUND
OR DRIVING.

00:42:07.133 --> 00:42:08.167
THIS IS REALLY COOL.

00:42:08.167 --> 00:42:09.601
THIS TECHNOLOGY
ACTUALLY GOT USED

00:42:09.601 --> 00:42:11.567
AT THE "SPIDERMAN 3" PREMIERE
IN L.A.

00:42:11.567 --> 00:42:13.834
SO THE AUDIENCE WAS CONTROLLING
SOMETHING ON THE SCREEN,

00:42:13.834 --> 00:42:16.501
SO THAT'S KIND OF NICE.

00:42:16.501 --> 00:42:18.901
AND I DON'T HAVE A CLASS PICTURE
FROM EVERY YEAR,

00:42:18.901 --> 00:42:20.667
BUT I DREDGED ALL THE ONES
THAT I DO HAVE,

00:42:20.667 --> 00:42:22.968
AND ALL I CAN SAY IS THAT
WHAT A PRIVILEGE

00:42:22.968 --> 00:42:24.701
AND AN HONOR IT WAS
TO TEACH THAT COURSE

00:42:24.701 --> 00:42:26.534
FOR SOMETHING LIKE TEN YEARS,

00:42:26.534 --> 00:42:30.734
AND ALL GOOD THINGS
COME TO AN END,

00:42:30.734 --> 00:42:34.567
AND I STOPPED TEACHING
THAT COURSE ABOUT A YEAR AGO.

00:42:34.567 --> 00:42:36.501
PEOPLE ALWAYS ASK ME
WHAT WAS MY FAVORITE MOMENT.

00:42:36.501 --> 00:42:38.868
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU COULD HAVE
A FAVORITE MOMENT,

00:42:38.868 --> 00:42:41.767
BUT, BOY, THERE IS ONE
I'LL NEVER FORGET.

00:42:41.767 --> 00:42:46.234
THIS WAS A WORLD WITH, I BELIEVE
A ROLLER-SKATING NINJA,

00:42:46.234 --> 00:42:48.501
AND ONE OF THE RULES WAS THAT
WE PERFORM THESE THINGS LIVE,

00:42:48.501 --> 00:42:49.801
AND THEY ALL HAD TO REALLY WORK,

00:42:49.801 --> 00:42:51.200
AND THE MOMENT
IT STOPPED WORKING,

00:42:51.200 --> 00:42:52.734
WE WENT TO
YOUR BACKUP VIDEOTAPE,

00:42:52.734 --> 00:42:54.901
AND THIS WAS VERY EMBARRASSING.

00:42:54.901 --> 00:42:56.767
SO WE HAVE THIS NINJA ON STAGE,

00:42:56.767 --> 00:42:58.467
AND HE'S DOING
THIS ROLLER-SKATING THING,

00:42:58.467 --> 00:43:00.834
AND THE WORLD,
IT DID NOT CRASH GENTLY.

00:43:00.834 --> 00:43:02.200
WHOOSH.

00:43:02.200 --> 00:43:03.534
AND I COME OUT,

00:43:03.534 --> 00:43:05.400
AND I BELIEVE
IT WAS STEVE AUDIA, WASN'T IT?

00:43:05.400 --> 00:43:07.200
WHERE IS HE?

00:43:07.200 --> 00:43:08.601
OKAY, WHERE IS STEVE?

00:43:08.601 --> 00:43:10.200
AH, MY MAN, STEVE AUDIA.

00:43:10.200 --> 00:43:13.467
AND TALK ABOUT
QUICK ON YOUR FEET, ALL RIGHT?

00:43:13.467 --> 00:43:16.267
I SAY, "STEVE, I'M SORRY,
BUT YOUR WORLD HAS CRASHED,

00:43:16.267 --> 00:43:19.000
AND WE'RE GOING TO GO
TO VIDEOTAPE."

00:43:19.000 --> 00:43:22.367
AND HE PULLS OUT HIS NINJA SWORD
AND SAYS,

00:43:22.367 --> 00:43:23.734
"I AM DISHONORED!
WHA!"

00:43:23.734 --> 00:43:25.267
AND JUST DROPS.

00:43:25.267 --> 00:43:28.200
[laughter and applause]

00:43:35.734 --> 00:43:37.100
AND SO I THINK
IT'S VERY TELLING

00:43:37.100 --> 00:43:38.267
THAT MY FAVORITE MOMENT

00:43:38.267 --> 00:43:40.067
IN TEN YEARS
OF THIS HIGH-TECHNOLOGY COURSE

00:43:40.067 --> 00:43:42.200
WAS A BRILLIANT AD-LIB.

00:43:42.200 --> 00:43:44.834
AND THEN WHEN THE VIDEOTAPE
IS DONE AND THE LIGHTS COME UP,

00:43:44.834 --> 00:43:49.534
HE'S LYING THERE LIFELESS,
AND HIS TEAMMATES DRAG HIM OFF.

00:43:49.534 --> 00:43:54.467
IT WAS REALLY
A FANTASTIC MOMENT.

00:43:54.467 --> 00:43:56.634
AND THE COURSE
WAS ALL ABOUT BONDING.

00:43:56.634 --> 00:43:57.834
PEOPLE USED TO SAY,
YOU KNOW,

00:43:57.834 --> 00:43:59.400
"WHAT'S GOING TO MAKE
FOR A GOOD WORLD?"

00:43:59.400 --> 00:44:00.968
I SAID, "I CAN'T
TELL YOU BEFOREHAND,

00:44:00.968 --> 00:44:02.400
"BUT RIGHT BEFORE
THEY PRESENT IT,

00:44:02.400 --> 00:44:03.734
"I CAN TELL YOU
IF THE WORLD'S GOOD

00:44:03.734 --> 00:44:05.000
"JUST BY THE BODY LANGUAGE.

00:44:05.000 --> 00:44:06.667
"IF THEY'RE STANDING
CLOSE TO EACH OTHER,

00:44:06.667 --> 00:44:08.968
THE WORLD IS GOOD."

00:44:08.968 --> 00:44:12.234
AND BVW
WAS A PIONEERING COURSE.

00:44:16.801 --> 00:44:19.334
I WON'T BORE YOU
WITH ALL THE DETAILS,

00:44:19.334 --> 00:44:22.767
BUT IT WASN'T EASY TO DO,

00:44:22.767 --> 00:44:25.634
AND I WAS GIVEN THIS WHEN
I STEPPED DOWN FROM THE ETC,

00:44:25.634 --> 00:44:27.234
AND I THINK IT'S EMBLEMATIC.

00:44:27.234 --> 00:44:29.167
IF YOU'RE GOING TO DO ANYTHING
THAT'S PIONEERING,

00:44:29.167 --> 00:44:30.834
YOU WILL GET THOSE ARROWS
IN THE BACK,

00:44:30.834 --> 00:44:32.200
AND YOU JUST HAVE
TO PUT UP WITH IT.

00:44:32.200 --> 00:44:34.234
I MEAN, EVERYTHING THAT
COULD GO WRONG DID GO WRONG,

00:44:34.234 --> 00:44:35.834
BUT AT THE END OF THE DAY,

00:44:35.834 --> 00:44:40.033
A WHOLE LOT OF PEOPLE
HAD A WHOLE LOT OF FUN.

00:44:40.033 --> 00:44:41.434
WHEN YOU'VE HAD SOMETHING FOR

00:44:41.434 --> 00:44:44.133
TEN YEARS THAT YOU HOLD
SO PRECIOUS,

00:44:44.133 --> 00:44:45.567
IT'S THE TOUGHEST THING
IN THE WORLD

00:44:45.567 --> 00:44:47.434
TO HAND IT OVER,

00:44:47.434 --> 00:44:48.868
AND THE ONLY ADVICE
I CAN GIVE YOU IS,

00:44:48.868 --> 00:44:52.067
FIND SOMEBODY BETTER THAN YOU
TO HAND IT TO,

00:44:52.067 --> 00:44:53.434
AND THAT'S WHAT I DID.

00:44:53.434 --> 00:44:57.834
THERE WAS THIS KID
AT THE VR STUDIO WAY BACK WHEN,

00:44:57.834 --> 00:44:59.334
AND YOU DIDN'T
HAVE TO SPEND VERY LONG

00:44:59.334 --> 00:45:01.801
IN JESSE SCHELL'S ORBIT TO GO,

00:45:01.801 --> 00:45:04.934
"THE FORCE IS STRONG
IN THIS ONE."

00:45:04.934 --> 00:45:06.667
AND ONE OF MY GREATEST--

00:45:06.667 --> 00:45:09.100
MY TWO GREATEST ACCOMPLISHMENTS,
I THINK, FOR CARNEGIE MELLON

00:45:09.100 --> 00:45:10.934
WERE THAT I GOT JESSICA HODGINS
AND JESSE SCHELL

00:45:10.934 --> 00:45:12.334
TO COME HERE
AND JOIN OUR FACULTY,

00:45:12.334 --> 00:45:14.501
AND I WAS THRILLED WHEN
I COULD HAND THIS OVER TO JESSE,

00:45:14.501 --> 00:45:16.133
AND TO NO ONE'S SURPRISE,

00:45:16.133 --> 00:45:18.234
HE HAS REALLY TAKEN IT UP
TO THE NEXT NOTCH,

00:45:18.234 --> 00:45:21.501
AND THE COURSE IS
IN MORE-THAN-GOOD HANDS.

00:45:21.501 --> 00:45:24.367
IT'S IN BETTER HANDS.

00:45:24.367 --> 00:45:26.601
BUT IT WAS JUST ONE COURSE,

00:45:26.601 --> 00:45:29.167
AND THEN WE REALLY TOOK IT
UP A NOTCH,

00:45:29.167 --> 00:45:34.200
AND WE CREATED WHAT I WOULD CALL
THE DREAM FULFILLMENT FACTORY.

00:45:34.200 --> 00:45:36.834
DON MARINELLI AND I
GOT TOGETHER,

00:45:36.834 --> 00:45:39.634
AND WITH THE UNIVERSITY'S
BLESSING AND ENCOURAGEMENT,

00:45:39.634 --> 00:45:42.100
WE MADE THIS THING
OUT OF WHOLE CLOTH

00:45:42.100 --> 00:45:43.834
THAT WAS ABSOLUTELY INSANE,

00:45:43.834 --> 00:45:45.901
SHOULD NEVER HAVE BEEN TRIED.

00:45:45.901 --> 00:45:50.801
ALL THE SANE UNIVERSITIES DIDN'T
GO NEAR THIS KIND OF STUFF,

00:45:50.801 --> 00:45:55.367
CREATING A TREMENDOUS
OPPORTUNISTIC VOID.

00:45:55.367 --> 00:45:57.000
SO THE ENTERTAINMENT
TECHNOLOGY CENTER

00:45:57.000 --> 00:45:58.601
WAS ALL ABOUT ARTISTS
AND TECHNOLOGISTS

00:45:58.601 --> 00:46:00.834
WORKING IN SMALL TEAMS
TO MAKE THINGS.

00:46:00.834 --> 00:46:03.200
IT WAS A TWO-YEAR PROFESSIONAL
MASTER'S DEGREE,

00:46:03.200 --> 00:46:06.100
AND DON AND I WERE
TWO KINDRED SPIRITS.

00:46:06.100 --> 00:46:07.234
WE'RE VERY DIFFERENT.

00:46:07.234 --> 00:46:08.267
ANYBODY WHO KNOWS US KNOWS

00:46:08.267 --> 00:46:11.267
THAT WE ARE
VERY DIFFERENT PEOPLE,

00:46:11.267 --> 00:46:13.367
AND WE LIKED TO DO THINGS
IN A NEW WAY,

00:46:13.367 --> 00:46:14.734
AND THE TRUTH
OF THE MATTER IS

00:46:14.734 --> 00:46:17.033
THAT WE ARE BOTH A LITTLE
UNCOMFORTABLE IN ACADEMIA.

00:46:17.033 --> 00:46:18.968
I USED TO SAY THAT I AM
UNCOMFORTABLE AS AN ACADEMIC

00:46:18.968 --> 00:46:20.501
BECAUSE I COME FROM A LONG LINE
OF PEOPLE

00:46:20.501 --> 00:46:25.634
WHO ACTUALLY WORKED
FOR A LIVING, SO...

00:46:25.634 --> 00:46:27.834
[laughter]

00:46:27.834 --> 00:46:31.434
I DETECT NERVOUS LAUGHTER.

00:46:31.434 --> 00:46:32.968
AND I WANT TO STRESS,
CARNEGIE MELLON

00:46:32.968 --> 00:46:34.234
IS THE ONLY PLACE
IN THE WORLD

00:46:34.234 --> 00:46:35.868
THAT THE ETC
COULD HAVE HAPPENED,

00:46:35.868 --> 00:46:37.801
BY FAR THE ONLY PLACE.

00:46:41.367 --> 00:46:46.367
OKAY, THIS PICTURE
WAS DON'S IDEA, OKAY?

00:46:46.367 --> 00:46:47.868
AND WE LIKE TO REFER
TO THIS PICTURE

00:46:47.868 --> 00:46:54.033
AS DON MARINELLI ON GUITAR
AND RANDY PAUSCH ON KEYBOARDS.

00:46:54.033 --> 00:46:56.100
BUT WE REALLY DID PLAY UP
THE LEFT BRAIN, RIGHT BRAIN,

00:46:56.100 --> 00:46:57.868
AND IT WORKED OUT REALLY WELL
THAT WAY.

00:46:57.868 --> 00:47:01.467
DON IS AN INTENSE GUY.

00:47:01.467 --> 00:47:04.400
[laughter and applause]

00:47:07.567 --> 00:47:11.434
AND DON AND I SHARED AN OFFICE,

00:47:11.434 --> 00:47:13.634
AND AT FIRST
IT WAS A SMALL OFFICE.

00:47:13.634 --> 00:47:18.067
WE SHARED AN OFFICE
FOR SIX YEARS, ALL RIGHT?

00:47:18.067 --> 00:47:21.801
NOW, THOSE OF YOU WHO KNOW DON
KNOW HE'S AN INTENSE GUY,

00:47:21.801 --> 00:47:23.634
AND, YOU KNOW,
GIVEN MY CURRENT CONDITION,

00:47:23.634 --> 00:47:25.968
SOMEBODY WAS ASKING ME--
THIS IS A TERRIBLE JOKE,

00:47:25.968 --> 00:47:28.634
BUT I'M GOING TO USE IT ANYWAY,

00:47:28.634 --> 00:47:30.400
BECAUSE I KNOW DON
WILL FORGIVE ME.

00:47:30.400 --> 00:47:32.300
SOMEBODY SAID,
"GIVEN YOUR CURRENT CONDITION,

00:47:32.300 --> 00:47:33.567
"HAVE YOU THOUGHT ABOUT

00:47:33.567 --> 00:47:35.834
WHETHER YOU'RE GONNA GO
TO HEAVEN OR HELL?"

00:47:35.834 --> 00:47:37.834
AND I SAID, "I DON'T KNOW,
BUT IF I'M GOING TO HELL,

00:47:37.834 --> 00:47:41.734
I'M DUE SIX YEARS
FOR TIME SERVED."

00:47:41.734 --> 00:47:43.501
I KID.

00:47:43.501 --> 00:47:45.067
SHARING AN OFFICE WITH DON

00:47:45.067 --> 00:47:48.067
WAS REALLY LIKE SHARING
AN OFFICE WITH A TORNADO.

00:47:48.067 --> 00:47:49.367
THERE WAS JUST SO MUCH ENERGY,

00:47:49.367 --> 00:47:53.067
AND YOU NEVER KNEW
WHICH TRAILER WAS NEXT, RIGHT?

00:47:53.067 --> 00:47:56.801
BUT YOU KNEW SOMETHING EXCITING
WAS GOING TO HAPPEN,

00:47:56.801 --> 00:47:59.133
AND THERE WAS SO MUCH ENERGY,

00:47:59.133 --> 00:48:02.100
AND I DO BELIEVE IN GIVING
CREDIT WHERE CREDIT IS DUE.

00:48:02.100 --> 00:48:04.667
SO IN MY TYPICALLY VISUAL WAY,

00:48:04.667 --> 00:48:07.501
IF DON AND I WERE TO SPLIT
THE SUCCESS FOR THE ETC,

00:48:07.501 --> 00:48:09.000
HE CLEARLY GETS
THE LION'S SHARE OF IT.

00:48:09.000 --> 00:48:11.167
HE DID THE LION'S SHARE
OF THE WORK, OKAY.

00:48:11.167 --> 00:48:12.901
HE HAD THE LION'S SHARE
OF THE IDEAS.

00:48:12.901 --> 00:48:14.033
IT WAS A GREAT TEAMWORK.

00:48:14.033 --> 00:48:15.667
I THINK IT WAS A GREAT YIN
AND A YANG,

00:48:15.667 --> 00:48:19.234
BUT IT WAS MORE LIKE "YIN"
AND YANG.

00:48:19.234 --> 00:48:21.167
AND HE DESERVES THAT CREDIT,
AND I GIVE IT TO HIM,

00:48:21.167 --> 00:48:23.100
BECAUSE THE ETC
IS A WONDERFUL PLACE,

00:48:23.100 --> 00:48:26.100
AND HE'S NOW RUNNING IT,
AND HE'S TAKING IT GLOBAL.

00:48:26.100 --> 00:48:27.801
WE'LL TALK ABOUT THAT
IN A SECOND.

00:48:27.801 --> 00:48:29.667
DESCRIBING THE ETC
IS REALLY HARD,

00:48:29.667 --> 00:48:31.334
AND I FINALLY FOUND
A METAPHOR.

00:48:31.334 --> 00:48:33.367
TELLING PEOPLE ABOUT THE ETC

00:48:33.367 --> 00:48:35.067
IS LIKE DESCRIBING
CIRQUE DU SOLEIL

00:48:35.067 --> 00:48:36.400
IF THEY'VE NEVER SEEN IT.

00:48:36.400 --> 00:48:38.334
SOONER OR LATER YOU'RE GOING
TO MAKE THE MISTAKE.

00:48:38.334 --> 00:48:39.701
YOU'RE GOING TO SAY,
"WELL, IT'S LIKE A CIRCUS."

00:48:39.701 --> 00:48:41.133
AND THEN YOU'RE DRAGGED
INTO THIS CONVERSATION ABOUT,

00:48:41.133 --> 00:48:42.601
"OH, HOW MANY TIGERS;
HOW MANY LIONS;

00:48:42.601 --> 00:48:44.801
ALL RIGHT,
HOW MANY TRAPEZE ACTS?"

00:48:44.801 --> 00:48:46.067
AND THAT MISSES THE WHOLE POINT.

00:48:46.067 --> 00:48:47.634
SO WHEN WE SAY WE'RE
A MASTER'S DEGREE,

00:48:47.634 --> 00:48:48.868
WE'RE REALLY NOT LIKE

00:48:48.868 --> 00:48:50.400
ANY MASTER'S DEGREE
YOU'VE EVER SEEN.

00:48:50.400 --> 00:48:52.634
HERE'S THE CURRICULUM.

00:48:58.133 --> 00:48:59.934
THE CURRICULUM ENDED UP
LOOKING LIKE THIS.

00:48:59.934 --> 00:49:01.801
ALL I WANT TO DO
IS VISUALLY COMMUNICATE TO YOU

00:49:01.801 --> 00:49:03.968
THAT YOU DO FIVE PROJECTS
IN BUILDING VIRTUAL WORLDS.

00:49:03.968 --> 00:49:05.367
THEN YOU DO THREE MORE.

00:49:05.367 --> 00:49:08.501
ALL OF YOUR TIME IS SPENT
IN SMALL TEAMS MAKING STUFF,

00:49:08.501 --> 00:49:09.901
NONE OF THAT
BOOK-LEARNING THING.

00:49:09.901 --> 00:49:12.033
DON AND I HAD NO PATIENCE
FOR THE BOOK-LEARNING THING.

00:49:12.033 --> 00:49:13.467
IT'S A MASTER'S DEGREE.

00:49:13.467 --> 00:49:15.434
THEY ALREADY SPENT FOUR YEARS
DOING BOOK LEARNING.

00:49:15.434 --> 00:49:20.667
ALL RIGHT, BY NOW THEY SHOULD
HAVE READ ALL THE BOOKS.

00:49:20.667 --> 00:49:21.868
THE KEYS TO SUCCESS

00:49:21.868 --> 00:49:25.634
WERE THAT CARNEGIE MELLON
GAVE US THE REINS,

00:49:25.634 --> 00:49:27.067
COMPLETELY GAVE US THE REINS.

00:49:27.067 --> 00:49:28.501
WE HAD NO DEANS TO REPORT TO.

00:49:28.501 --> 00:49:29.968
WE REPORTED DIRECTLY
TO THE PROVOST,

00:49:29.968 --> 00:49:31.434
WHICH IS GREAT,
BECAUSE THE PROVOST

00:49:31.434 --> 00:49:34.501
IS WAY TOO BUSY
TO WATCH YOU CAREFULLY.

00:49:34.501 --> 00:49:37.067
WE WERE GIVEN EXPLICIT LICENSE
TO BREAK THE MOLD.

00:49:37.067 --> 00:49:38.334
IT WAS ALL PROJECT BASED.

00:49:38.334 --> 00:49:39.334
IT WAS INTENSE.

00:49:39.334 --> 00:49:41.534
IT WAS FUN,
AND WE TOOK FIELD TRIPS.

00:49:41.534 --> 00:49:43.534
EVERY SPRING SEMESTER
IN JANUARY,

00:49:43.534 --> 00:49:45.701
WE'D TAKE ALL 50 STUDENTS
IN THE FIRST-YEAR CLASS,

00:49:45.701 --> 00:49:47.567
AND WE'D TAKE THEM OUT
TO SHOPS AT PIXAR.

00:49:47.567 --> 00:49:49.534
WE'D TAKE 'EM TO PIXAR,
INDUSTRIAL LIGHT AND MAGIC,

00:49:49.534 --> 00:49:50.901
AND OF COURSE
WHEN YOU'VE GOT GUYS

00:49:50.901 --> 00:49:53.801
LIKE TOMMY THERE ACTING AS HOST,
RIGHT,

00:49:53.801 --> 00:49:56.234
IT'S PRETTY EASY TO GET ENTREE
TO THESE PLACES.

00:49:56.234 --> 00:49:58.968
SO WE DID THINGS VERY,
VERY DIFFERENTLY.

00:49:58.968 --> 00:50:00.601
THE KIND OF PROJECTS
STUDENTS WOULD DO,

00:50:00.601 --> 00:50:03.467
WE DID A LOT OF WHAT WE'D CALL
EDU-TAINMENT.

00:50:03.467 --> 00:50:04.667
WE DEVELOPED
A BUNCH OF THINGS

00:50:04.667 --> 00:50:06.234
WITH THE FIRE DEPARTMENT
OF NEW YORK,

00:50:06.234 --> 00:50:08.167
A NETWORK SIMULATOR
FOR TRAINING FIREFIGHTERS,

00:50:08.167 --> 00:50:10.167
USING VIDEO GAME-ISH TYPE
TECHNOLOGY

00:50:10.167 --> 00:50:12.133
TO TEACH PEOPLE USEFUL THINGS.

00:50:12.133 --> 00:50:14.334
THAT'S NOT BAD.

00:50:14.334 --> 00:50:15.801
COMPANIES DID
THIS STRANGE THING.

00:50:15.801 --> 00:50:20.467
THEY PUT IN WRITING, "WE PROMISE
TO HIRE YOUR STUDENTS."

00:50:20.467 --> 00:50:22.167
I'VE GOT THE EA
AND ACTIVISION ONES HERE.

00:50:22.167 --> 00:50:25.234
I THINK THERE ARE NOW,
HOW MANY, FIVE?

00:50:25.234 --> 00:50:27.434
DREW KNOWS, I BET.

00:50:27.434 --> 00:50:29.067
SO THERE ARE FIVE
WRITTEN AGREEMENTS.

00:50:29.067 --> 00:50:30.534
I DON'T KNOW OF ANY OTHER SCHOOL

00:50:30.534 --> 00:50:32.734
THAT HAS THIS KIND OF WRITTEN
AGREEMENT WITH ANY COMPANY,

00:50:32.734 --> 00:50:34.267
AND SO THAT'S A REAL STATEMENT.

00:50:34.267 --> 00:50:35.734
AND THESE ARE
MULTIPLE-YEAR THINGS,

00:50:35.734 --> 00:50:37.200
SO THEY'RE AGREEING
TO HIRE PEOPLE

00:50:37.200 --> 00:50:39.834
FOR SUMMER INTERNSHIPS
THAT WE HAVE NOT ADMITTED YET.

00:50:39.834 --> 00:50:41.200
THAT'S A PRETTY STRONG STATEMENT

00:50:41.200 --> 00:50:43.167
ABOUT THE QUALITY
OF THE PROGRAM.

00:50:43.167 --> 00:50:45.801
AND DON, AS I SAID, HE'S NOW--
HE'S CRAZY.

00:50:45.801 --> 00:50:48.367
I MEAN THAT IN A WONDERFUL
COMPLIMENTARY WAY.

00:50:48.367 --> 00:50:52.200
HE'S DOING THESE THINGS
WHERE I'M LIKE, "OH, MY GOD."

00:50:52.200 --> 00:50:54.734
HE'S NOT HERE TONIGHT,
BECAUSE HE'S IN SINGAPORE,

00:50:54.734 --> 00:50:57.300
BECAUSE THERE'S GOING TO BE
AN ETC CAMPUS IN SINGAPORE.

00:50:57.300 --> 00:50:58.734
THERE'S ALREADY ONE
IN AUSTRALIA,

00:50:58.734 --> 00:51:00.167
AND THERE'S GOING TO BE ONE
IN KOREA.

00:51:00.167 --> 00:51:01.901
SO THIS IS BECOMING
A GLOBAL PHENOMENON.

00:51:01.901 --> 00:51:03.501
SO I THINK THIS
REALLY SPEAKS VOLUMES

00:51:03.501 --> 00:51:04.901
ABOUT ALL
THE OTHER UNIVERSITIES.

00:51:04.901 --> 00:51:06.467
IT'S REALLY TRUE
THAT CARNEGIE MELLON

00:51:06.467 --> 00:51:08.067
IS THE ONLY UNIVERSITY
THAT CAN DO THIS.

00:51:08.067 --> 00:51:12.434
WE JUST HAVE TO DO IT
ALL OVER THE WORLD NOW.

00:51:12.434 --> 00:51:14.133
ONE OTHER BIG SUCCESS
ABOUT THE ETC

00:51:14.133 --> 00:51:16.767
IS TEACHING PEOPLE
ABOUT FOCUS--

00:51:16.767 --> 00:51:21.367
OH, I HEAR THE NERVOUS LAUGHTER
FROM THE STUDENTS.

00:51:21.367 --> 00:51:23.367
I HAD FORGOTTEN THE DELAYED
SHOCK THERAPY EFFECT

00:51:23.367 --> 00:51:25.234
OF THESE BAR CHARTS.

00:51:25.234 --> 00:51:27.167
WHEN YOU'RE TAKING
BUILDING VIRTUAL WORLDS,

00:51:27.167 --> 00:51:28.834
EVERY TWO WEEKS
WE GET PEER FEEDBACK.

00:51:28.834 --> 00:51:30.367
WE PUT THAT ALL
INTO A BIG SPREADSHEET,

00:51:30.367 --> 00:51:31.767
AND AT THE END OF THE SEMESTER,

00:51:31.767 --> 00:51:33.501
YOU HAD THREE TEAMMATES
PER PROJECT,

00:51:33.501 --> 00:51:34.567
FIVE PROJECTS.

00:51:34.567 --> 00:51:35.601
THAT'S 15 DATA POINTS.

00:51:35.601 --> 00:51:36.868
THAT'S STATISTICALLY VALID.

00:51:36.868 --> 00:51:39.367
AND YOU GET A BAR CHART
TELLING YOU ON A RANKING

00:51:39.367 --> 00:51:40.634
OF HOW EASY YOU ARE
TO WORK WITH,

00:51:40.634 --> 00:51:43.367
WHERE YOU STACK UP
AGAINST YOUR PEERS.

00:51:43.367 --> 00:51:46.601
BOY, THAT'S HARD FEEDBACK
TO IGNORE.

00:51:46.601 --> 00:51:49.000
SOME STILL MANAGED.

00:51:49.000 --> 00:51:52.400
[laughter]

00:51:52.400 --> 00:51:54.501
BUT FOR THE MOST PART,
PEOPLE LOOKED AT THAT AND WENT,

00:51:54.501 --> 00:51:56.634
"WOW, I'VE GOT TO PICK IT UP
A NOTCH.

00:51:56.634 --> 00:51:58.467
"I BETTER START THINKING ABOUT
WHAT I'M SAYING

00:51:58.467 --> 00:51:59.701
TO PEOPLE IN THESE MEETINGS."

00:51:59.701 --> 00:52:02.400
AND THAT IS THE BEST GIFT
AN EDUCATOR CAN GIVE

00:52:02.400 --> 00:52:05.467
IS TO GET SOMEBODY
TO BECOME SELF-REFLECTIVE.

00:52:05.467 --> 00:52:06.901
SO THE ETC WAS WONDERFUL,

00:52:06.901 --> 00:52:10.601
BUT EVEN THE ETC AND EVEN AS DON
SCALES IT AROUND THE GLOBE,

00:52:10.601 --> 00:52:14.200
IT'S STILL VERY LABOR INTENSIVE,
YOU KNOW.

00:52:14.200 --> 00:52:15.634
IT'S NOT TOMMY
ONE AT A TIME.

00:52:15.634 --> 00:52:18.167
IT'S NOT A RESEARCH GROUP
TEN AT A TIME.

00:52:18.167 --> 00:52:21.834
IT'S 50 OR 100 AT A TIME
PER CAMPUS TIMES FOUR CAMPUSES.

00:52:21.834 --> 00:52:25.734
BUT I WANTED SOMETHING
INFINITELY SCALABLE, ALL RIGHT?

00:52:25.734 --> 00:52:27.400
SCALABLE TO THE POINT
WHERE MILLIONS

00:52:27.400 --> 00:52:29.234
OR TENS OF MILLIONS
OF PEOPLE

00:52:29.234 --> 00:52:31.734
COULD CHASE THEIR DREAMS
WITH SOMETHING.

00:52:31.734 --> 00:52:33.934
AND, YOU KNOW,
I GUESS THAT KIND OF A GOAL

00:52:33.934 --> 00:52:37.067
REALLY DOES MAKE ME
THE MAD HATTER.

00:52:37.067 --> 00:52:42.801
SO ALICE IS A PROJECT THAT WE'VE
WORKED ON FOR A LONG, LONG TIME.

00:52:42.801 --> 00:52:45.968
IT'S A NOVEL WAY
TO TEACH COMPUTER PROGRAMMING.

00:52:45.968 --> 00:52:47.400
KIDS MAKE MOVIES AND GAMES,

00:52:47.400 --> 00:52:49.601
THE HEAD FAKE--AGAIN,
WE'RE BACK TO THE HEAD FAKES.

00:52:49.601 --> 00:52:51.434
THE BEST WAY
TO TEACH SOMEBODY SOMETHING

00:52:51.434 --> 00:52:54.100
IS TO HAVE THEM THINK
THEY'RE LEARNING SOMETHING ELSE.

00:52:54.100 --> 00:52:55.667
I'VE DONE IT MY WHOLE CAREER.

00:52:55.667 --> 00:52:57.934
AND THE HEAD FAKE HERE IS THAT
THEY'RE LEARNING TO PROGRAM,

00:52:57.934 --> 00:53:00.200
BUT THEY JUST THINK THEY'RE
MAKING MOVIES AND VIDEO GAMES.

00:53:00.200 --> 00:53:01.834
THIS THING
HAS ALREADY BEEN DOWNLOADED

00:53:01.834 --> 00:53:03.234
WELL OVER A MILLION TIMES.

00:53:03.234 --> 00:53:05.534
THERE ARE EIGHT TEXTBOOKS
THAT HAVE BEEN WRITTEN ABOUT IT.

00:53:05.534 --> 00:53:07.367
10% OF U.S. COLLEGES
ARE USING IT NOW,

00:53:07.367 --> 00:53:09.467
AND IT'S NOT THE GOOD STUFF YET.

00:53:09.467 --> 00:53:14.367
THE GOOD STUFF IS COMING
IN THE NEXT VERSION.

00:53:14.367 --> 00:53:16.868
I, LIKE MOSES, GET TO SEE
THE PROMISED LAND,

00:53:16.868 --> 00:53:19.667
BUT I WON'T GET
TO SET FOOT IN IT,

00:53:19.667 --> 00:53:22.667
AND THAT'S OKAY,
BECAUSE I CAN SEE IT,

00:53:22.667 --> 00:53:25.300
AND THE VISION IS CLEAR:

00:53:25.300 --> 00:53:30.067
MILLIONS OF KIDS HAVING FUN
WHILE LEARNING SOMETHING HARD.

00:53:30.067 --> 00:53:32.000
THAT'S PRETTY COOL.

00:53:32.000 --> 00:53:34.200
I CAN DEAL WITH THAT
AS A LEGACY.

00:53:34.200 --> 00:53:35.968
THE NEXT VERSION'S
GOING TO COME OUT IN 2008.

00:53:35.968 --> 00:53:37.667
IT'S GOING TO BE TEACHING
THE JAVA LANGUAGE

00:53:37.667 --> 00:53:39.501
IF YOU WANT THEM TO KNOW
THEY'RE LEARNING JAVA.

00:53:39.501 --> 00:53:40.701
OTHERWISE THEY'LL JUST THINK

00:53:40.701 --> 00:53:42.534
THAT THEY'RE WRITING
MOVIE SCRIPTS.

00:53:42.534 --> 00:53:45.734
AND WE'RE GETTING THE CHARACTERS

00:53:45.734 --> 00:53:48.834
FROM THE BEST-SELLING PC GAME
IN HISTORY, "THE SIMS."

00:53:48.834 --> 00:53:50.901
AND THIS IS ALL ALREADY
WORKING IN THE LAB,

00:53:50.901 --> 00:53:53.367
SO THERE'S NO REAL
TECHNOLOGICAL RISK.

00:53:53.367 --> 00:53:55.367
I DON'T HAVE TIME TO THANK
AND MENTION EVERYBODY

00:53:55.367 --> 00:53:56.601
IN THE ALICE TEAM,

00:53:56.601 --> 00:53:58.334
BUT I JUST WANT TO SAY THAT
DENNIS COSGROVE

00:53:58.334 --> 00:54:00.367
IS GOING TO BE BUILDING THIS,
HAS BEEN BUILDING THIS.

00:54:00.367 --> 00:54:01.868
HE IS THE DESIGNER.

00:54:01.868 --> 00:54:05.167
IT'S HIS BABY, AND FOR
THOSE OF YOU WHO ARE WONDERING,

00:54:05.167 --> 00:54:07.033
"WELL, YOU KNOW,
IN SOME NUMBER OF MONTHS,

00:54:07.033 --> 00:54:09.033
WHO SHOULD I BE EMAILING
ABOUT THE ALICE PROJECT,"

00:54:09.033 --> 00:54:11.634
WHERE'S WANDA DANN?

00:54:11.634 --> 00:54:12.767
OH, THERE YOU ARE.

00:54:12.767 --> 00:54:14.968
STAND UP,
LET THEM ALL SEE YOU.

00:54:14.968 --> 00:54:16.467
EVERYBODY SAY,
"HI, WANDA."

00:54:16.467 --> 00:54:18.434
all: HI, WANDA.

00:54:18.434 --> 00:54:21.167
Pausch: SEND HER THE EMAIL.

00:54:21.167 --> 00:54:23.300
AND I'LL TALK A LITTLE BIT MORE
ABOUT CAITLIN KELLEHER,

00:54:23.300 --> 00:54:25.267
BUT SHE'S GRADUATED
WITH HER PhD

00:54:25.267 --> 00:54:26.834
AND IS AT WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY,

00:54:26.834 --> 00:54:28.501
AND SHE'S GOING
TO BE TAKING THIS UP A NOTCH

00:54:28.501 --> 00:54:30.200
AND GOING TO MIDDLE SCHOOLS
WITH IT.

00:54:30.200 --> 00:54:33.801
SO GRAND VISION,
AND TO THE EXTENT

00:54:33.801 --> 00:54:35.300
THAT YOU CAN LIVE ON
IN SOMETHING,

00:54:35.300 --> 00:54:37.767
I WILL LIVE ON IN ALICE.

00:54:37.767 --> 00:54:39.501
ALL RIGHT, SO NOW THE THIRD PART
OF THE TALK,

00:54:39.501 --> 00:54:40.834
LESSONS LEARNED.

00:54:40.834 --> 00:54:42.367
WE'VE TALKED ABOUT MY DREAMS.

00:54:42.367 --> 00:54:45.033
WE'VE TALKED ABOUT HELPING OTHER
PEOPLE ENABLE THEIR DREAMS.

00:54:45.033 --> 00:54:46.300
SOMEWHERE ALONG THE WAY,

00:54:46.300 --> 00:54:47.601
THERE'S GOT TO BE SOME ASPECT

00:54:47.601 --> 00:54:51.334
OF WHAT LETS YOU GET
TO ACHIEVE YOUR DREAMS.

00:54:51.334 --> 00:54:54.734
FIRST ONE IS THE ROLE OF
PARENTS, MENTORS, AND STUDENTS.

00:54:54.734 --> 00:54:59.868
I WAS BLESSED TO HAVE BEEN BORN
TO TWO INCREDIBLE PEOPLE.

00:54:59.868 --> 00:55:04.234
THIS IS MY MOTHER
ON HER 70TH BIRTHDAY.

00:55:04.234 --> 00:55:05.734
I AM BACK HERE.

00:55:05.734 --> 00:55:09.467
I HAVE JUST BEEN LAPPED.

00:55:09.467 --> 00:55:13.934
THIS IS MY DAD RIDING A ROLLER
COASTER ON HIS 80TH BIRTHDAY,

00:55:13.934 --> 00:55:17.167
AND HE POINTS OUT THAT,
YOU KNOW, HE'S NOT ONLY BRAVE;

00:55:17.167 --> 00:55:18.567
HE'S TALENTED,

00:55:18.567 --> 00:55:21.934
BECAUSE HE DID WIN THAT BIG BEAR
THE SAME DAY.

00:55:21.934 --> 00:55:25.868
MY DAD WAS SO FULL OF LIFE.

00:55:25.868 --> 00:55:27.467
ANYTHING WITH HIM
WAS AN ADVENTURE.

00:55:27.467 --> 00:55:31.267
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S IN THAT BAG,
BUT I KNOW IT'S COOL.

00:55:31.267 --> 00:55:34.501
MY DAD DRESSED UP
AS SANTA CLAUS,

00:55:34.501 --> 00:55:39.000
BUT HE ALSO DID VERY,
VERY SIGNIFICANT THINGS

00:55:39.000 --> 00:55:40.601
TO HELP LOTS OF PEOPLE.

00:55:40.601 --> 00:55:44.200
THIS IS A DORMITORY IN THAILAND
THAT MY MOM AND DAD UNDERWROTE,

00:55:44.200 --> 00:55:47.467
AND EVERY YEAR, ABOUT
30 STUDENTS GET TO GO TO SCHOOL

00:55:47.467 --> 00:55:48.734
WHO WOULDN'T HAVE OTHERWISE.

00:55:48.734 --> 00:55:50.000
THIS IS SOMETHING

00:55:50.000 --> 00:55:51.901
MY WIFE AND I HAVE
ALSO BEEN INVOLVED IN HEAVILY,

00:55:51.901 --> 00:55:53.400
AND THESE ARE
THE KIND OF THINGS

00:55:53.400 --> 00:55:56.834
THAT I THINK EVERYBODY OUGHT
TO BE DOING, HELPING OTHERS.

00:55:56.834 --> 00:55:59.167
BUT THE BEST STORY
I HAVE ABOUT MY DAD IS--

00:55:59.167 --> 00:56:00.601
UNFORTUNATELY
MY DAD PASSED AWAY

00:56:00.601 --> 00:56:01.901
A LITTLE OVER A YEAR AGO,

00:56:01.901 --> 00:56:03.701
AND WHEN WE WERE GOING
THROUGH HIS THINGS--

00:56:03.701 --> 00:56:05.901
HE HAD FOUGHT IN WORLD WAR II
IN THE BATTLE OF THE BULGE--

00:56:05.901 --> 00:56:07.634
AND WHEN WE WERE GOING
THROUGH HIS THINGS,

00:56:07.634 --> 00:56:11.868
WE FOUND OUT HE HAD BEEN AWARDED
THE BRONZE STAR FOR VALOR.

00:56:11.868 --> 00:56:13.701
MY MOM DIDN'T KNOW IT.

00:56:13.701 --> 00:56:20.200
IN 50 YEARS OF MARRIAGE,
IT HAD JUST NEVER COME UP.

00:56:20.200 --> 00:56:21.634
MY MOM.

00:56:21.634 --> 00:56:26.167
MOTHERS ARE PEOPLE WHO LOVE YOU
EVEN WHEN YOU PULL THEIR HAIR.

00:56:26.167 --> 00:56:28.267
AND I HAVE TWO
GREAT MOM STORIES.

00:56:28.267 --> 00:56:30.434
WHEN I WAS HERE STUDYING
TO GET MY PhD

00:56:30.434 --> 00:56:33.334
AND I WAS TAKING SOMETHING
CALLED THE THEORY QUALIFIER,

00:56:33.334 --> 00:56:34.968
WHICH I CAN DEFINITIVELY SAY

00:56:34.968 --> 00:56:38.367
IS THE SECOND WORST THING
IN MY LIFE AFTER CHEMOTHERAPY...

00:56:38.367 --> 00:56:41.734
[laughter]

00:56:41.734 --> 00:56:43.534
AND I WAS COMPLAINING
TO MY MOTHER

00:56:43.534 --> 00:56:45.200
ABOUT HOW HARD
THIS TEST WAS

00:56:45.200 --> 00:56:47.767
AND HOW AWFUL IT WAS,
AND SHE JUST LEANED OVER,

00:56:47.767 --> 00:56:49.367
AND SHE PATTED ME ON THE ARM,
AND SHE SAID,

00:56:49.367 --> 00:56:51.567
"WE KNOW HOW YOU FEEL, HONEY,
AND REMEMBER,

00:56:51.567 --> 00:56:54.334
WHEN YOUR FATHER WAS YOUR AGE,
HE WAS FIGHTING THE GERMANS."

00:56:54.334 --> 00:56:57.267
[laughter]

00:57:01.667 --> 00:57:04.234
AFTER I GOT MY PhD,
MY MOTHER TOOK GREAT RELISH

00:57:04.234 --> 00:57:06.033
IN INTRODUCING ME AS,
"THIS IS MY SON.

00:57:06.033 --> 00:57:08.734
HE'S A DOCTOR BUT NOT THE KIND
WHO HELPS PEOPLE."

00:57:08.734 --> 00:57:11.667
[laughter]

00:57:14.133 --> 00:57:15.634
THESE SLIDES
ARE A LITTLE BIT DARK,

00:57:15.634 --> 00:57:17.934
BUT WHEN I WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL,
I DECIDED TO PAINT MY BEDROOM.

00:57:17.934 --> 00:57:21.667
I'D ALWAYS WANTED A SUBMARINE
AND AN ELEVATOR.

00:57:21.667 --> 00:57:23.834
AND THE GREAT THING ABOUT THIS--

00:57:23.834 --> 00:57:26.767
[laughter]

00:57:29.434 --> 00:57:31.868
WHAT CAN I SAY?

00:57:31.868 --> 00:57:33.267
AND THE GREAT THING
ABOUT THIS IS,

00:57:33.267 --> 00:57:35.000
THEY LET ME DO IT,

00:57:35.000 --> 00:57:36.501
AND THEY DIDN'T
GET UPSET ABOUT IT,

00:57:36.501 --> 00:57:38.167
AND IT'S STILL THERE.

00:57:38.167 --> 00:57:40.567
IF YOU GO TO MY PARENT'S HOUSE,
IT'S STILL THERE.

00:57:40.567 --> 00:57:42.434
AND ANYBODY WHO IS OUT THERE
WHO IS A PARENT,

00:57:42.434 --> 00:57:44.767
IF YOUR KIDS WANT TO PAINT
THEIR BEDROOM,

00:57:44.767 --> 00:57:47.200
AS A FAVOR TO ME,
LET THEM DO IT, OKAY?

00:57:47.200 --> 00:57:48.934
IT'LL BE OKAY.

00:57:48.934 --> 00:57:52.634
DON'T WORRY ABOUT RESALE VALUE
ON THE HOUSE.

00:57:52.634 --> 00:57:55.667
OTHER PEOPLE WHO HELP US BESIDES
OUR PARENTS: OUR TEACHERS,

00:57:55.667 --> 00:57:58.601
OUR MENTORS, OUR FRIENDS,
OUR COLLEAGUES.

00:57:58.601 --> 00:58:02.400
GOD, WHAT IS THERE TO SAY
ABOUT ANDY VAN DAM?

00:58:02.400 --> 00:58:04.701
WHEN I WAS A FRESHMAN AT BROWN,
HE WAS ON LEAVE,

00:58:04.701 --> 00:58:07.200
AND ALL I HEARD ABOUT
WAS THIS ANDY VAN DAM.

00:58:07.200 --> 00:58:10.100
HE WAS LIKE A MYTHICAL CREATURE,
LIKE A CENTAUR,

00:58:10.100 --> 00:58:13.067
BUT LIKE
A REALLY PISSED OFF CENTAUR,

00:58:13.067 --> 00:58:15.667
AND EVERYBODY WAS, LIKE,
REALLY SAD

00:58:15.667 --> 00:58:20.834
THAT HE WAS GONE
BUT KIND OF MORE RELAXED,

00:58:20.834 --> 00:58:22.000
AND I FOUND OUT WHY,

00:58:22.000 --> 00:58:23.767
BECAUSE I STARTED WORKING
FOR ANDY.

00:58:23.767 --> 00:58:25.701
I WAS A TEACHING ASSISTANT
FOR HIM AS A SOPHOMORE,

00:58:25.701 --> 00:58:27.868
AND I WAS QUITE
AN ARROGANT YOUNG MAN,

00:58:27.868 --> 00:58:30.968
AND I CAME IN
TO SOME OFFICE HOURS,

00:58:30.968 --> 00:58:32.300
AND OF COURSE IT WAS 9:00
AT NIGHT,

00:58:32.300 --> 00:58:33.701
AND ANDY WAS THERE
AT OFFICE HOURS,

00:58:33.701 --> 00:58:34.801
WHICH IS YOUR FIRST CLUE

00:58:34.801 --> 00:58:36.634
AS TO WHAT KIND OF PROFESSOR
HE WAS.

00:58:36.634 --> 00:58:38.701
AND I COME BOUNDING IN,
AND, YOU KNOW,

00:58:38.701 --> 00:58:40.267
I'M JUST--I'M GOING
TO SAVE THE WORLD.

00:58:40.267 --> 00:58:41.934
THERE'RE ALL THESE KIDS
WAITING FOR HELP,

00:58:41.934 --> 00:58:43.501
DA DA, DA DA, DA DA,
DA DA.

00:58:43.501 --> 00:58:46.133
AND AFTERWARDS, ANDY LITERALLY
DUTCH-UNCLED--HE'S DUTCH, RIGHT?

00:58:46.133 --> 00:58:47.267
HE DUTCH-UNCLED ME,

00:58:47.267 --> 00:58:48.801
AND HE PUT HIS ARM
AROUND MY SHOULDERS,

00:58:48.801 --> 00:58:49.968
AND WE WENT FOR A LITTLE WALK,

00:58:49.968 --> 00:58:53.367
AND HE SAID, "RANDY,
IT'S SUCH A SHAME

00:58:53.367 --> 00:58:58.367
"THAT PEOPLE PERCEIVE YOU
AS SO ARROGANT,

00:58:58.367 --> 00:59:00.868
"BECAUSE IT'S GOING TO LIMIT

00:59:00.868 --> 00:59:04.701
WHAT YOU'RE GOING TO BE ABLE
TO ACCOMPLISH IN LIFE."

00:59:04.701 --> 00:59:08.667
WHAT A HELL OF A GOOD WAY
TO WORD "YOU'RE BEING A JERK."

00:59:08.667 --> 00:59:09.968
RIGHT?

00:59:09.968 --> 00:59:11.300
HE DOESN'T SAY,
"YOU'RE A JERK."

00:59:11.300 --> 00:59:13.100
HE SAYS, "PEOPLE ARE PERCEIVING
YOU THIS WAY,"

00:59:13.100 --> 00:59:15.033
AND HE SAYS, "THE DOWNSIDE IS,
IT'S GOING TO LIMIT

00:59:15.033 --> 00:59:17.400
WHAT YOU'RE GOING
TO BE ABLE TO ACCOMPLISH."

00:59:17.400 --> 00:59:20.901
WHEN I GOT TO KNOW ANDY BETTER,
THE BEATINGS BECAME MORE DIRECT.

00:59:20.901 --> 00:59:24.701
[laughter]

00:59:24.701 --> 00:59:26.434
I COULD TELL YOU ANDY STORIES
FOR A MONTH,

00:59:26.434 --> 00:59:28.801
BUT THE ONE I WILL TELL YOU
IS THAT WHEN IT CAME TIME

00:59:28.801 --> 00:59:30.133
TO START THINKING
ABOUT WHAT TO DO

00:59:30.133 --> 00:59:31.367
AFTER GRADUATING FROM BROWN,

00:59:31.367 --> 00:59:33.133
IT HAD NEVER OCCURRED TO ME
IN A MILLION YEARS

00:59:33.133 --> 00:59:35.501
TO GO TO GRADUATE SCHOOL,
JUST OUT OF MY IMAGINATION.

00:59:35.501 --> 00:59:38.367
IT WASN'T THE KIND OF THING
PEOPLE FROM MY FAMILY DID.

00:59:38.367 --> 00:59:39.801
WE GOT, SAY,
WHAT DO YOU CALL THEM?

00:59:39.801 --> 00:59:42.000
JOBS.

00:59:42.000 --> 00:59:44.667
AND ANDY SAID,
"NO, DON'T GO DO THAT.

00:59:44.667 --> 00:59:46.601
GO GET A PhD.
BECOME A PROFESSOR."

00:59:46.601 --> 00:59:48.200
AND I SAID, "WHY?"

00:59:48.200 --> 00:59:52.300
AND HE SAID, "BECAUSE
YOU'RE SUCH A GOOD SALESMAN

00:59:52.300 --> 00:59:53.634
"THAT ANY COMPANY WHO GETS YOU

00:59:53.634 --> 00:59:55.667
"IS GOING TO USE YOU
AS A SALESMAN,

00:59:55.667 --> 00:59:58.200
"AND YOU MIGHT AS WELL
BE SELLING

00:59:58.200 --> 01:00:01.133
SOMETHING WORTHWHILE
LIKE EDUCATION."

01:00:06.067 --> 01:00:09.167
THANKS.

01:00:09.167 --> 01:00:12.367
ANDY WAS MY FIRST BOSS,
SO TO SPEAK.

01:00:12.367 --> 01:00:15.634
I WAS LUCKY ENOUGH TO HAVE
A LOT OF BOSSES.

01:00:15.634 --> 01:00:16.968
THAT RED CIRCLE IS WAY OFF.

01:00:16.968 --> 01:00:19.634
AL IS OVER HERE.

01:00:19.634 --> 01:00:22.167
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL
HAPPENED THERE.

01:00:22.167 --> 01:00:24.133
HE'S PROBABLY WATCHING THIS
ON THE WEBCAST GOING,

01:00:24.133 --> 01:00:29.534
"MY GOD, HE'S TARGETING,
AND HE STILL CAN'T AIM!"

01:00:29.534 --> 01:00:31.667
I DON'T WANT TO SAY MUCH
ABOUT THE GREAT BOSSES I'VE HAD

01:00:31.667 --> 01:00:33.467
EXCEPT THAT THEY WERE GREAT,

01:00:33.467 --> 01:00:35.901
AND I KNOW A LOT OF PEOPLE IN
THE WORLD HAVE HAD BAD BOSSES,

01:00:35.901 --> 01:00:37.901
AND I HAVEN'T HAD TO ENDURE
THAT EXPERIENCE,

01:00:37.901 --> 01:00:39.634
AND I'M VERY GRATEFUL
TO ALL OF THE PEOPLE

01:00:39.634 --> 01:00:41.067
THAT I EVER HAD TO REPORT TO.

01:00:41.067 --> 01:00:42.701
THEY'VE JUST BEEN INCREDIBLE.

01:00:42.701 --> 01:00:44.634
BUT IT'S NOT
JUST OUR BOSSES.

01:00:44.634 --> 01:00:45.834
WE LEARN FROM OUR STUDENTS.

01:00:45.834 --> 01:00:47.734
I THINK THE BEST HEAD FAKE
OF ALL TIME

01:00:47.734 --> 01:00:49.267
COMES FROM CAITLIN KELLEHER--

01:00:49.267 --> 01:00:52.033
EXCUSE ME,
DR. CAITLIN KELLEHER--

01:00:52.033 --> 01:00:53.133
WHO JUST FINISHED UP HERE

01:00:53.133 --> 01:00:54.834
AND IS STARTING
AT WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY,

01:00:54.834 --> 01:00:56.501
AND SHE LOOKED AT ALICE

01:00:56.501 --> 01:00:58.267
WHEN IT WAS AN EASIER WAY
TO LEARN TO PROGRAM,

01:00:58.267 --> 01:01:00.767
AND SHE SAID, "YEAH,
BUT WHY IS THAT FUN?"

01:01:00.767 --> 01:01:03.367
I WAS LIKE, "WELL,
'CAUSE I'M A COMPULSIVE MALE.

01:01:03.367 --> 01:01:05.367
"I LIKE TO MAKE THE LITTLE TOY
SOLDIERS MOVE AROUND

01:01:05.367 --> 01:01:08.501
BY MY COMMAND,
AND THAT'S FUN."

01:01:08.501 --> 01:01:10.501
SHE'S LIKE, "HMM."

01:01:10.501 --> 01:01:11.968
AND SHE WAS THE ONE WHO SAID,

01:01:11.968 --> 01:01:14.868
"NO, WE'LL JUST APPROACH IT ALL
AS A STORYTELLING ACTIVITY."

01:01:14.868 --> 01:01:17.667
AND SHE'S DONE WONDERFUL WORK
SHOWING THAT,

01:01:17.667 --> 01:01:19.267
PARTICULARLY WITH
MIDDLE SCHOOL GIRLS,

01:01:19.267 --> 01:01:21.067
IF YOU PRESENT IT
AS A STORYTELLING ACTIVITY,

01:01:21.067 --> 01:01:22.501
THEY'RE PERFECTLY WILLING
TO LEARN

01:01:22.501 --> 01:01:24.033
HOW TO WRITE COMPUTER SOFTWARE.

01:01:24.033 --> 01:01:27.033
SO ALL-TIME BEST
HEAD FAKE AWARD

01:01:27.033 --> 01:01:31.067
GOES TO CAITLIN KELLEHER'S
DISSERTATION.

01:01:31.067 --> 01:01:32.734
PRESIDENT COHON,
WHEN I TOLD HIM

01:01:32.734 --> 01:01:33.934
I WAS GOING TO DO THIS TALK,

01:01:33.934 --> 01:01:37.167
HE SAID, "PLEASE TELL THEM
ABOUT HAVING FUN,

01:01:37.167 --> 01:01:41.133
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT
I REMEMBER YOU FOR."

01:01:41.133 --> 01:01:43.167
AND I SAID, "I CAN DO THAT,
BUT IT'S KIND OF LIKE A FISH

01:01:43.167 --> 01:01:46.067
TALKING ABOUT THE IMPORTANCE
OF WATER."

01:01:46.067 --> 01:01:48.934
I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO NOT HAVE FUN.

01:01:48.934 --> 01:01:52.200
ALL RIGHT, I'M DYING,
AND I'M HAVING FUN,

01:01:52.200 --> 01:01:56.934
AND I'M GOING TO KEEP HAVING FUN
EVERY DAY I HAVE LEFT,

01:01:56.934 --> 01:01:59.467
BECAUSE THERE'S NO OTHER WAY
TO PLAY IT.

01:01:59.467 --> 01:02:00.734
ALL RIGHT?

01:02:00.734 --> 01:02:02.868
SO MY NEXT PIECE OF ADVICE IS,

01:02:02.868 --> 01:02:04.767
YOU JUST HAVE TO DECIDE
IF YOU'RE A TIGGER

01:02:04.767 --> 01:02:06.601
OR YOU'RE AN EEYORE.

01:02:06.601 --> 01:02:08.667
I THINK I'M CLEAR WHERE I STAND

01:02:08.667 --> 01:02:13.534
ON THE GREAT
TIGGER-EEYORE DEBATE.

01:02:13.534 --> 01:02:17.033
NEVER LOSE THE CHILDLIKE WONDER.

01:02:17.033 --> 01:02:18.634
IT'S JUST TOO IMPORTANT.

01:02:18.634 --> 01:02:20.200
IT'S WHAT DRIVES US.

01:02:20.200 --> 01:02:22.501
HELP OTHERS.

01:02:22.501 --> 01:02:25.601
DENNY PROFFITT KNOWS MORE ABOUT
HELPING OTHER PEOPLE.

01:02:25.601 --> 01:02:27.801
HE'S FORGOTTEN MORE
THAN I'LL EVER KNOW.

01:02:27.801 --> 01:02:29.934
HE'S TAUGHT ME BY EXAMPLE
HOW TO RUN A GROUP,

01:02:29.934 --> 01:02:31.767
HOW TO CARE ABOUT PEOPLE.

01:02:31.767 --> 01:02:32.901
M.K. HALEY--
I HAVE A THEORY

01:02:32.901 --> 01:02:34.534
THAT PEOPLE WHO COME
FROM LARGE FAMILIES

01:02:34.534 --> 01:02:35.834
ARE BETTER PEOPLE,

01:02:35.834 --> 01:02:37.834
BECAUSE THEY'VE JUST HAD
TO LEARN HOW TO GET ALONG.

01:02:37.834 --> 01:02:41.167
M.K. HALEY COMES FROM A FAMILY
WITH 20 KIDS.

01:02:41.167 --> 01:02:43.968
YEAH, UNBELIEVABLE.

01:02:43.968 --> 01:02:46.834
AND SHE ALWAYS SAYS, "IT'S KIND
OF FUN TO DO THE IMPOSSIBLE."

01:02:46.834 --> 01:02:48.234
WHEN I FIRST GOT
TO IMAGINEERING,

01:02:48.234 --> 01:02:50.100
SHE WAS ONE OF THE PEOPLE
WHO DRESSED ME DOWN,

01:02:50.100 --> 01:02:51.601
AND SHE SAID, "I UNDERSTAND

01:02:51.601 --> 01:02:53.100
"YOU'VE JOINED
THE ALADDIN PROJECT.

01:02:53.100 --> 01:02:54.734
WHAT CAN YOU DO?"

01:02:54.734 --> 01:02:57.567
AND I SAID, "WELL, I'M A TENURED
PROFESSOR OF COMPUTER SCIENCE."

01:02:57.567 --> 01:02:59.801
AND SHE SAID, "WELL,
THAT'S VERY NICE PROFESSOR BOY,

01:02:59.801 --> 01:03:01.300
"BUT THAT'S NOT WHAT I ASKED.

01:03:01.300 --> 01:03:02.868
I SAID, 'WHAT CAN YOU DO?'"

01:03:02.868 --> 01:03:05.801
[laughter]

01:03:09.901 --> 01:03:15.400
AND, YOU KNOW, I MENTIONED
SORT OF MY WORKING-CLASS ROOTS.

01:03:15.400 --> 01:03:17.567
WE KEEP WHAT IS VALUABLE TO US,
WHAT WE CHERISH,

01:03:17.567 --> 01:03:19.767
AND I'VE KEPT MY LETTERMAN'S
JACKET ALL THESE YEARS.

01:03:19.767 --> 01:03:22.033
I USED TO LIKE WEARING IT
IN GRAD SCHOOL,

01:03:22.033 --> 01:03:25.934
AND ONE OF MY FRIENDS,
JESSICA HODGINS WOULD SAY,

01:03:25.934 --> 01:03:28.067
"WHY DO YOU WEAR
THIS LETTERMAN'S JACKET?"

01:03:28.067 --> 01:03:30.567
AND I LOOKED AROUND AT ALL
THE NON-ATHLETIC GUYS AROUND ME

01:03:30.567 --> 01:03:35.234
WHO WERE MUCH SMARTER THAN ME,
AND I SAID, "BECAUSE I CAN."

01:03:35.234 --> 01:03:38.133
AND SO SHE THOUGHT
THAT WAS A REAL HOOT,

01:03:38.133 --> 01:03:42.167
SO ONE YEAR SHE MADE FOR ME
THIS LITTLE RAGGEDY RANDY DOLL.

01:03:42.167 --> 01:03:44.567
HE'S GOT A LITTLE
LETTERMAN'S JACKET TOO.

01:03:44.567 --> 01:03:46.300
THAT'S MY ALL-TIME FAVORITE.

01:03:46.300 --> 01:03:50.100
IT'S THE PERFECT GIFT FOR
THE EGOMANIAC IN YOUR LIFE.

01:03:50.100 --> 01:03:55.334
SO I'VE MET SO MANY
WONDERFUL PEOPLE ALONG THE WAY.

01:03:55.334 --> 01:03:57.200
LOYALTY IS A TWO-WAY STREET.

01:03:57.200 --> 01:03:59.167
THERE WAS A YOUNG MAN
NAMED DENNIS COSGROVE

01:03:59.167 --> 01:04:05.133
AT THE UNIVERSITY OF VIRGINIA,
AND WHEN HE WAS A YOUNG MAN,

01:04:05.133 --> 01:04:09.000
LET'S JUST SAY THINGS HAPPENED,

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:13.901
AND I FOUND MYSELF TALKING
TO A DEAN, AND THE DEAN--

01:04:13.901 --> 01:04:17.234
NO, NOT THAT DEAN.

01:04:17.234 --> 01:04:19.167
AND ANYWAY, THIS DEAN
REALLY HAD IT IN FOR DENNIS,

01:04:19.167 --> 01:04:20.167
AND I COULD NEVER
FIGURE OUT WHY,

01:04:20.167 --> 01:04:21.200
BECAUSE DENNIS
WAS A FINE FELLOW,

01:04:21.200 --> 01:04:22.200
BUT FOR SOME REASON,

01:04:22.200 --> 01:04:23.567
THIS DEAN REALLY HAD IT
IN FOR HIM.

01:04:23.567 --> 01:04:25.767
AND I ENDED UP BASICALLY SAYING,
"NO, I VOUCH FOR DENNIS."

01:04:25.767 --> 01:04:27.868
AND THE GUY SAYS, "YOU'RE NOT
EVEN TENURED YET,

01:04:27.868 --> 01:04:30.267
AND YOU'RE TELLING ME
YOU'RE GOING TO VOUCH

01:04:30.267 --> 01:04:32.067
FOR THIS SOPHOMORE OR JUNIOR
OR WHATEVER?"

01:04:32.067 --> 01:04:33.400
I THINK HE WAS A JUNIOR
AT THE TIME.

01:04:33.400 --> 01:04:35.000
I SAID, "YEAH, I'M GOING
TO VOUCH FOR HIM,

01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:36.300
BECAUSE I BELIEVE IN HIM."

01:04:36.300 --> 01:04:38.234
AND THE DEAN SAID,
"AND I'M GOING TO REMEMBER THIS

01:04:38.234 --> 01:04:40.133
WHEN YOUR TENURE CASE
COMES UP."

01:04:40.133 --> 01:04:41.534
AND I SAID, "DEAL."

01:04:41.534 --> 01:04:43.601
I WENT BACK TO TALK TO DENNIS,
AND I SAID,

01:04:43.601 --> 01:04:48.934
"I WOULD REALLY APPRECIATE YOU--
THAT WOULD BE GOOD."

01:04:48.934 --> 01:04:50.400
BUT LOYALTY IS A TWO-WAY STREET.

01:04:50.400 --> 01:04:52.534
I MEAN, THAT WAS GOD KNOWS
HOW MANY YEARS AGO,

01:04:52.534 --> 01:04:55.033
BUT THAT'S THE SAME
DENNIS COSGROVE

01:04:55.033 --> 01:04:57.033
WHO'S CARRYING ALICE FORWARD.

01:04:57.033 --> 01:04:59.267
HE'S BEEN WITH ME
ALL THESE YEARS, ALL RIGHT.

01:04:59.267 --> 01:05:01.634
AND, YOU KNOW,
IF WE ONLY HAD ONE PERSON

01:05:01.634 --> 01:05:02.968
TO SEND IN
A SPACE PROBE

01:05:02.968 --> 01:05:08.701
TO MEET AN ALIEN SPECIES,
I'M PICKING DENNIS.

01:05:08.701 --> 01:05:10.267
YOU CAN'T GIVE A TALK
AT CARNEGIE MELLON

01:05:10.267 --> 01:05:13.534
WITHOUT ACKNOWLEDGING
ONE VERY SPECIAL PERSON,

01:05:13.534 --> 01:05:16.067
AND THAT WOULD BE SHARON BURKS.

01:05:16.067 --> 01:05:17.300
I JOKED WITH HER.

01:05:17.300 --> 01:05:18.901
I SAID, "WELL, LOOK,
IF YOU'RE RETIRING,

01:05:18.901 --> 01:05:20.701
IT'S JUST NOT WORTH
LIVING ANYMORE."

01:05:20.701 --> 01:05:24.234
[laughter]

01:05:24.234 --> 01:05:26.868
SHARON IS SO WONDERFUL,
IT'S BEYOND DESCRIPTION,

01:05:26.868 --> 01:05:28.901
AND FOR ALL OF US WHO
HAVE BEEN HELPED BY HER,

01:05:28.901 --> 01:05:30.534
IT'S JUST INDESCRIBABLE.

01:05:30.534 --> 01:05:31.567
I LOVE THIS PICTURE,

01:05:31.567 --> 01:05:33.100
BECAUSE IT PUTS
HER TOGETHER WITH SYL,

01:05:33.100 --> 01:05:34.467
AND SYL IS GREAT,

01:05:34.467 --> 01:05:38.300
BECAUSE SYL GAVE THE BEST PIECE
OF ADVICE POUND FOR POUND

01:05:38.300 --> 01:05:39.701
THAT I HAVE EVER HEARD,

01:05:39.701 --> 01:05:42.601
AND I THINK ALL YOUNG LADIES
SHOULD HEAR THIS.

01:05:42.601 --> 01:05:44.200
SYL SAID, "IT TOOK ME
A LONG TIME,

01:05:44.200 --> 01:05:46.200
"BUT I'VE
FINALLY FIGURED IT OUT.

01:05:46.200 --> 01:05:49.968
"WHEN IT COMES TO MEN THAT ARE
ROMANTICALLY INTERESTED IN YOU,

01:05:49.968 --> 01:05:51.767
"IT'S REALLY SIMPLE.

01:05:51.767 --> 01:05:54.634
"JUST IGNORE EVERYTHING THEY SAY

01:05:54.634 --> 01:05:58.200
"AND ONLY PAY ATTENTION
TO WHAT THEY DO.

01:05:58.200 --> 01:06:01.200
IT'S THAT SIMPLE.
IT'S THAT EASY."

01:06:01.200 --> 01:06:03.400
AND I THOUGHT BACK
TO MY BACHELOR DAYS,

01:06:03.400 --> 01:06:06.000
AND I SAID, "DAMN."

01:06:09.567 --> 01:06:11.200
NEVER GIVE UP.

01:06:11.200 --> 01:06:12.934
I DIDN'T GET
INTO BROWN UNIVERSITY.

01:06:12.934 --> 01:06:14.667
I WAS ON THE WAIT LIST.

01:06:14.667 --> 01:06:17.968
I CALLED THEM UP,
AND THEY EVENTUALLY DECIDED

01:06:17.968 --> 01:06:20.234
THAT IT WAS GETTING
REALLY ANNOYING

01:06:20.234 --> 01:06:23.100
TO HAVE ME CALL EVERY DAY,
SO THEY LET ME IN.

01:06:23.100 --> 01:06:25.267
AT CARNEGIE MELLON, I DIDN'T
GET INTO GRADUATE SCHOOL.

01:06:25.267 --> 01:06:26.267
ANDY HAD MENTORED ME.

01:06:26.267 --> 01:06:27.501
HE SAID, "GO TO GRADUATE SCHOOL.

01:06:27.501 --> 01:06:28.968
"YOU'RE GOING
TO CARNEGIE MELLON.

01:06:28.968 --> 01:06:31.734
ALL MY GOOD STUDENTS
GO TO CARNEGIE MELLON."

01:06:31.734 --> 01:06:33.601
AND, YEAH,
YOU KNOW WHAT'S COMING.

01:06:33.601 --> 01:06:35.734
AND SO HE SAID, "YOU'RE GOING
TO GO TO CARNEGIE MELLON,

01:06:35.734 --> 01:06:37.067
NO PROBLEM."

01:06:37.067 --> 01:06:39.200
WHAT HE HAD KIND OF FORGOTTEN
WAS THAT THE DIFFICULTY

01:06:39.200 --> 01:06:41.601
OF GETTING INTO THE TOP
PhD PROGRAM IN THE COUNTRY

01:06:41.601 --> 01:06:43.200
HAD REALLY GONE UP,

01:06:43.200 --> 01:06:46.567
AND HE ALSO DIDN'T KNOW
I WAS GOING TO TANK MY GREs,

01:06:46.567 --> 01:06:48.033
BECAUSE HE BELIEVED IN ME,

01:06:48.033 --> 01:06:49.534
WHICH,
BASED ON MY BOARD SCORES,

01:06:49.534 --> 01:06:51.534
WAS A REALLY STUPID IDEA,

01:06:51.534 --> 01:06:53.300
AND SO I DIDN'T
GET INTO CARNEGIE MELLON.

01:06:53.300 --> 01:06:54.400
NO ONE KNOWS THIS TILL TODAY.

01:06:54.400 --> 01:06:55.567
I'M TELLING THE STORY.

01:06:55.567 --> 01:06:57.667
I WAS DECLINED ADMISSION
TO CARNEGIE MELLON,

01:06:57.667 --> 01:07:02.767
AND I WAS A BIT
OF AN OBNOXIOUS LITTLE KID.

01:07:02.767 --> 01:07:04.133
I WENT INTO ANDY'S OFFICE,

01:07:04.133 --> 01:07:06.300
AND I DROPPED THE REJECTION
LETTER ON HIS DESK.

01:07:06.300 --> 01:07:07.801
AND I SAID, "I JUST WANT YOU
TO KNOW

01:07:07.801 --> 01:07:09.667
"WHAT YOUR LETTER
OF RECOMMENDATION GOES FOR

01:07:09.667 --> 01:07:10.934
AT CARNEGIE MELLON."

01:07:10.934 --> 01:07:13.868
[laughter]

01:07:18.634 --> 01:07:22.000
AND BEFORE THE LETTER
HAD HIT HIS DESK,

01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:24.234
HIS HAND WAS ON THE PHONE,
AND HE SAID,

01:07:24.234 --> 01:07:26.501
"I WILL FIX THIS."

01:07:26.501 --> 01:07:30.167
[laughter]

01:07:30.167 --> 01:07:31.234
AND I SAID, "NO, NO, NO,

01:07:31.234 --> 01:07:32.501
"I DON'T WANT TO DO IT THAT WAY.

01:07:32.501 --> 01:07:33.801
"THAT'S NOT THE WAY
I WAS RAISED.

01:07:33.801 --> 01:07:35.634
"YOU KNOW, MAYBE SOME OTHER
GRADUATE SCHOOLS

01:07:35.634 --> 01:07:37.968
WILL SEE FIT TO ADMIT ME."
AND HE SAID, "LOOK.

01:07:37.968 --> 01:07:39.868
CARNEGIE MELLON'S
WHERE YOU'RE GONNA BE."

01:07:39.868 --> 01:07:41.767
HE SAID, "I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.
I'LL MAKE YOU A DEAL.

01:07:41.767 --> 01:07:42.968
GO VISIT THE OTHER SCHOOLS."

01:07:42.968 --> 01:07:44.734
BECAUSE I DID GET INTO
ALL THE OTHER SCHOOLS.

01:07:44.734 --> 01:07:46.200
HE SAID, "GO VISIT
THE OTHER SCHOOLS,

01:07:46.200 --> 01:07:48.400
"AND IF YOU REALLY DON'T
FEEL COMFORTABLE AT ANY OF THEM,

01:07:48.400 --> 01:07:51.000
THEN WILL YOU LET ME CALL NICO?"
NICO BEING NICO HABERMANN.

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:53.501
AND I SAID, "OKAY, DEAL."
I WENT TO THE OTHER SCHOOLS.

01:07:53.501 --> 01:07:58.133
WITHOUT NAMING THEM BY NAME--
BERKELEY, CORNELL--

01:07:58.133 --> 01:08:00.300
THEY MANAGED TO BE
SO UNWELCOMING

01:08:00.300 --> 01:08:01.801
THAT I FOUND MYSELF
SAYING TO ANDY,

01:08:01.801 --> 01:08:03.534
"YOU KNOW,
I'M GOING TO GET A JOB."

01:08:03.534 --> 01:08:05.267
AND HE SAID, "NO, YOU'RE NOT,"

01:08:05.267 --> 01:08:08.200
AND HE PICKED UP THE PHONE,
AND HE TALKED IN DUTCH.

01:08:08.200 --> 01:08:11.000
[laughter]

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:13.200
AND HE HUNG UP THE PHONE,
AND HE SAID,

01:08:13.200 --> 01:08:14.934
"NICO SAYS IF YOU'RE SERIOUS,

01:08:14.934 --> 01:08:19.901
BE IN HIS OFFICE
TOMORROW MORNING AT 8:00 A.M."

01:08:19.901 --> 01:08:22.434
AND FOR THOSE OF YOU
WHO KNOW NICO,

01:08:22.434 --> 01:08:24.400
THIS IS REALLY SCARY.

01:08:24.400 --> 01:08:25.734
SO I'M IN
NICO HABERMANN'S OFFICE

01:08:25.734 --> 01:08:26.968
THE NEXT MORNING
AT 8:00 A.M.,

01:08:26.968 --> 01:08:29.167
AND HE'S TALKING WITH ME,
AND FRANKLY,

01:08:29.167 --> 01:08:31.734
I DON'T THINK HE'S THAT KEEN
ON THIS MEETING.

01:08:31.734 --> 01:08:33.167
I DON'T THINK HE'S
THAT KEEN AT ALL.

01:08:33.167 --> 01:08:39.234
AND HE SAYS, "RANDY,
WHY ARE WE HERE?"

01:08:39.234 --> 01:08:43.734
AND I SAID,
"BECAUSE ANDY PHONED YOU?"

01:08:43.734 --> 01:08:48.167
AND I SAID, "WELL,
SINCE YOU ADMITTED ME,

01:08:48.167 --> 01:08:50.033
"I HAVE WON A FELLOWSHIP.

01:08:50.033 --> 01:08:51.767
"THE OFFICE OF NAVAL RESEARCH,

01:08:51.767 --> 01:08:53.300
"IT'S A VERY PRESTIGIOUS
FELLOWSHIP.

01:08:53.300 --> 01:08:54.501
"I'VE WON THIS FELLOWSHIP,

01:08:54.501 --> 01:08:56.601
AND THAT WASN'T IN MY FILE
WHEN I APPLIED."

01:08:56.601 --> 01:09:00.968
AND NICO SAID, "A FELLOWSHIP,
MONEY, WE HAVE PLENTY OF MONEY."

01:09:00.968 --> 01:09:04.634
THAT WAS BACK THEN.

01:09:04.634 --> 01:09:06.033
HE SAID, "WE HAVE PLENTY
OF MONEY.

01:09:06.033 --> 01:09:07.868
"WHY DO YOU THINK
HAVING A FELLOWSHIP

01:09:07.868 --> 01:09:09.734
MAKES ANY DIFFERENCE TO US?"

01:09:09.734 --> 01:09:10.934
AND HE LOOKED AT ME.

01:09:10.934 --> 01:09:13.367
THERE ARE MOMENTS
THAT CHANGE YOUR LIFE,

01:09:13.367 --> 01:09:14.734
AND TEN YEARS LATER,

01:09:14.734 --> 01:09:17.267
IF YOU KNOW IN RETROSPECT
IT WAS ONE OF THOSE MOMENTS,

01:09:17.267 --> 01:09:18.667
YOU'RE BLESSED,

01:09:18.667 --> 01:09:22.701
BUT TO KNOW IT AT THE MOMENT

01:09:22.701 --> 01:09:27.367
WITH NICO
STARING THROUGH YOUR SOUL...

01:09:27.367 --> 01:09:28.767
AND I SAID, "I DIDN'T MEAN
TO IMPLY

01:09:28.767 --> 01:09:30.133
"ANYTHING ABOUT THE MONEY.

01:09:30.133 --> 01:09:31.367
"IT'S JUST THAT
IT WAS AN HONOR.

01:09:31.367 --> 01:09:32.901
"THERE WERE ONLY
15 GIVEN NATIONWIDE,

01:09:32.901 --> 01:09:34.133
"AND I DID THINK
IT WAS AN HONOR

01:09:34.133 --> 01:09:36.834
"THAT WOULD BE SOMETHING
THAT WOULD BE MERITORIOUS,

01:09:36.834 --> 01:09:41.133
AND I APOLOGIZE
IF THAT WAS PRESUMPTUOUS."

01:09:41.133 --> 01:09:44.834
AND HE SMILED,
AND THAT WAS GOOD.

01:09:44.834 --> 01:09:47.133
SO HOW DO YOU GET PEOPLE
TO HELP YOU?

01:09:47.133 --> 01:09:48.400
YOU CAN'T GET THERE ALONE.

01:09:48.400 --> 01:09:51.667
PEOPLE HAVE TO HELP YOU,
AND I DO BELIEVE IN KARMA.

01:09:51.667 --> 01:09:52.667
I BELIEVE IN PAYBACKS.

01:09:52.667 --> 01:09:53.767
YOU GET PEOPLE TO HELP YOU

01:09:53.767 --> 01:09:55.734
BY TELLING THE TRUTH,
BEING EARNEST.

01:09:55.734 --> 01:09:59.133
I'LL TAKE AN EARNEST PERSON
OVER A HIP PERSON EVERY DAY,

01:09:59.133 --> 01:10:00.300
BECAUSE HIP IS SHORT-TERM.

01:10:00.300 --> 01:10:02.801
EARNEST IS LONG-TERM.

01:10:02.801 --> 01:10:07.067
APOLOGIZE WHEN YOU SCREW UP
AND FOCUS ON OTHER PEOPLE,

01:10:07.067 --> 01:10:08.167
NOT ON YOURSELF.

01:10:08.167 --> 01:10:10.734
AND I THOUGHT,
HOW DO I POSSIBLY

01:10:10.734 --> 01:10:13.100
MAKE A CONCRETE EXAMPLE
OF THAT?

01:10:13.100 --> 01:10:14.634
DO WE HAVE A CONCRETE EXAMPLE

01:10:14.634 --> 01:10:16.734
OF FOCUSING ON SOMEBODY ELSE
OVER THERE?

01:10:16.734 --> 01:10:18.400
COULD WE BRING IT OUT?

01:10:18.400 --> 01:10:20.901
SEE, YESTERDAY
WAS MY WIFE'S BIRTHDAY.

01:10:20.901 --> 01:10:23.601
IF THERE WAS EVER A TIME
I MIGHT BE ENTITLED

01:10:23.601 --> 01:10:24.734
TO HAVE THE FOCUS ON ME,

01:10:24.734 --> 01:10:27.367
IT MIGHT BE
THE LAST LECTURE.

01:10:27.367 --> 01:10:29.100
BUT NO, I FEEL VERY BADLY

01:10:29.100 --> 01:10:31.167
THAT MY WIFE DIDN'T REALLY GET
A PROPER BIRTHDAY,

01:10:31.167 --> 01:10:33.934
AND I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE
VERY NICE IF 500 PEOPLE--

01:10:33.934 --> 01:10:36.868
[applause]

01:10:53.434 --> 01:10:56.534
all singing:
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU.

01:10:56.534 --> 01:10:57.601
Pausch: HER NAME IS JAI.

01:10:57.601 --> 01:11:00.968
all singing:
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU.

01:11:00.968 --> 01:11:05.567
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DEAR JAI.

01:11:05.567 --> 01:11:09.734
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU.

01:11:09.734 --> 01:11:12.667
[cheers and applause]

01:11:18.667 --> 01:11:20.601
Pausch: YOU GOT
TO BLOW IT OUT.

01:11:27.367 --> 01:11:28.567
ALL RIGHT.

01:11:28.567 --> 01:11:31.501
[applause]

01:11:37.834 --> 01:11:39.601
AND NOW YOU ALL HAVE
AN EXTRA REASON

01:11:39.601 --> 01:11:43.601
TO COME TO THE RECEPTION.

01:11:43.601 --> 01:11:46.567
REMEMBER, BRICK WALLS LET US
SHOW OUR DEDICATION.

01:11:46.567 --> 01:11:48.300
THEY ARE THERE TO SEPARATE US

01:11:48.300 --> 01:11:50.100
FROM THE PEOPLE
WHO DON'T REALLY WANT

01:11:50.100 --> 01:11:51.734
TO ACHIEVE
THEIR CHILDHOOD DREAMS.

01:11:51.734 --> 01:11:53.467
DON'T BAIL.

01:11:53.467 --> 01:11:56.100
THE BEST OF THE GOLD IS AT
THE BOTTOM OF BARRELS OF CRAP.

01:11:56.100 --> 01:11:59.033
[laughter]

01:12:01.234 --> 01:12:07.834
WHAT STEVE DIDN'T TELL YOU
WAS THE BIG SABBATICAL AT EA.

01:12:07.834 --> 01:12:11.200
I HAD BEEN THERE FOR 48 HOURS,
AND THEY LOVED THE ETC.

01:12:11.200 --> 01:12:12.334
WE WERE THE BEST.

01:12:12.334 --> 01:12:13.601
WE WERE THE FAVORITES,

01:12:13.601 --> 01:12:15.701
AND THEN SOMEBODY ELSE
PULLED ME ASIDE AND SAID,

01:12:15.701 --> 01:12:16.968
"OH, BY THE WAY,

01:12:16.968 --> 01:12:18.734
"WE'RE ABOUT TO GIVE $8 MILLION
TO USC

01:12:18.734 --> 01:12:20.200
"TO BUILD A PROGRAM
JUST LIKE YOURS.

01:12:20.200 --> 01:12:22.234
WE'RE HOPING YOU CAN HELP THEM
GET IT OFF THE GROUND."

01:12:22.234 --> 01:12:25.167
[laughter]

01:12:27.467 --> 01:12:28.868
AND THEN STEVE CAME ALONG
AND SAID,

01:12:28.868 --> 01:12:31.567
"THEY SAID WHAT?
OH, GOD."

01:12:31.567 --> 01:12:35.934
AND TO QUOTE A FAMOUS MAN,
"I WILL FIX THIS."

01:12:35.934 --> 01:12:37.200
AND HE DID.

01:12:37.200 --> 01:12:39.133
STEVE HAS BEEN
AN INCREDIBLE PARTNER,

01:12:39.133 --> 01:12:40.567
AND WE HAVE
A GREAT RELATIONSHIP,

01:12:40.567 --> 01:12:42.701
PERSONAL AND PROFESSIONAL,

01:12:42.701 --> 01:12:44.267
AND HE HAS CERTAINLY
BEEN POINT MAN

01:12:44.267 --> 01:12:48.601
ON GETTING A GAMING ASSET
TO HELP TEACH MILLIONS OF KIDS,

01:12:48.601 --> 01:12:51.067
AND, YOU KNOW,
THAT'S JUST INCREDIBLE.

01:12:51.067 --> 01:12:53.934
BUT, YOU KNOW, IT CERTAINLY
WOULD HAVE BEEN REASONABLE

01:12:53.934 --> 01:12:57.300
FOR ME TO LEAVE 48 HOURS
INTO THAT SABBATICAL,

01:12:57.300 --> 01:13:00.000
BUT IT WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN
THE RIGHT THING TO DO,

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:01.734
AND WHEN YOU DO
THE RIGHT THING,

01:13:01.734 --> 01:13:05.767
GOOD STUFF HAS A WAY
OF HAPPENING.

01:13:05.767 --> 01:13:07.968
GET A FEEDBACK LOOP
AND LISTEN TO IT.

01:13:07.968 --> 01:13:10.501
YOUR FEEDBACK LOOP CAN BE THIS
DORKY SPREADSHEET THING I DID,

01:13:10.501 --> 01:13:12.033
OR IT CAN JUST BE ONE GREAT MAN

01:13:12.033 --> 01:13:14.000
WHO TELLS YOU
WHAT YOU NEED TO HEAR.

01:13:14.000 --> 01:13:16.267
THE HARD PART
IS THE LISTENING TO IT.

01:13:16.267 --> 01:13:18.534
ANYBODY CAN GET CHEWED OUT.

01:13:18.534 --> 01:13:21.334
IT'S THE RARE PERSON WHO SAYS,
"OH, MY GOD, YOU'RE RIGHT,"

01:13:21.334 --> 01:13:23.801
AS OPPOSED TO, "NO WAIT,
THE REAL REASON IS"--

01:13:23.801 --> 01:13:25.267
WE'VE ALL HEARD THAT.

01:13:25.267 --> 01:13:28.801
WHEN PEOPLE GIVE YOU FEEDBACK,
CHERISH IT AND USE IT.

01:13:28.801 --> 01:13:30.667
SHOW GRATITUDE.

01:13:30.667 --> 01:13:33.100
WHEN I GOT TENURE,
I TOOK ALL OF MY RESEARCH TEAM

01:13:33.100 --> 01:13:34.968
DOWN TO DISNEYWORLD FOR A WEEK,

01:13:34.968 --> 01:13:37.000
AND ONE OF THE OTHER PROFESSORS
AT VIRGINIA SAID,

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:39.067
"HOW CAN YOU DO THAT?"

01:13:39.067 --> 01:13:40.868
I SAID, "THESE PEOPLE
JUST BUSTED THEIR ASS

01:13:40.868 --> 01:13:42.667
"AND GOT ME THE BEST JOB
IN THE WORLD FOR LIFE.

01:13:42.667 --> 01:13:46.033
HOW COULD I NOT DO THAT?"
RIGHT?

01:13:46.033 --> 01:13:49.534
DON'T COMPLAIN;
JUST WORK HARDER.

01:13:49.534 --> 01:13:51.067
THAT'S A PICTURE
OF JACKIE ROBINSON.

01:13:51.067 --> 01:13:52.601
IT WAS IN HIS CONTRACT
NOT TO COMPLAIN,

01:13:52.601 --> 01:13:56.601
EVEN WHEN THE FANS
SPIT ON HIM.

01:13:56.601 --> 01:14:00.267
BE GOOD AT SOMETHING;
IT MAKES YOU VALUABLE.

01:14:00.267 --> 01:14:02.367
WORK HARD.

01:14:02.367 --> 01:14:04.200
I GOT TENURE A YEAR EARLY
AS STEVE MENTIONED.

01:14:04.200 --> 01:14:05.801
JUNIOR FACULTY MEMBERS
USED TO SAY TO ME,

01:14:05.801 --> 01:14:07.100
"WOW, YOU GOT TENURE EARLY.

01:14:07.100 --> 01:14:09.267
WHAT'S YOUR SECRET?"

01:14:09.267 --> 01:14:10.567
I SAID, "IT'S PRETTY SIMPLE.

01:14:10.567 --> 01:14:12.467
"CALL ME ANY FRIDAY NIGHT
IN MY OFFICE AT 10:00,

01:14:12.467 --> 01:14:15.200
AND I'LL TELL YOU."

01:14:15.200 --> 01:14:16.300
FIND THE BEST IN EVERYBODY.

01:14:16.300 --> 01:14:17.634
ONE OF THE THINGS
THAT JON SNODDY,

01:14:17.634 --> 01:14:19.133
AS I SAID, TOLD ME

01:14:19.133 --> 01:14:22.801
IS THAT YOU MIGHT HAVE TO WAIT
A LONG TIME, SOMETIMES YEARS,

01:14:22.801 --> 01:14:25.501
BUT PEOPLE WILL SHOW YOU
THEIR GOOD SIDE.

01:14:25.501 --> 01:14:29.934
JUST KEEP WAITING, NO MATTER
HOW LONG IT TAKES.

01:14:29.934 --> 01:14:31.901
NO ONE IS ALL EVIL.

01:14:31.901 --> 01:14:32.901
EVERYBODY HAS A GOOD SIDE.

01:14:32.901 --> 01:14:33.901
JUST KEEP WAITING.

01:14:33.901 --> 01:14:34.934
IT WILL COME OUT.

01:14:34.934 --> 01:14:36.200
AND BE PREPARED.

01:14:36.200 --> 01:14:39.868
LUCK IS TRULY WHERE PREPARATION
MEETS OPPORTUNITY.

01:14:39.868 --> 01:14:43.133
SO TODAY'S TALK
WAS ABOUT MY CHILDHOOD DREAMS,

01:14:43.133 --> 01:14:49.167
ENABLING THE DREAMS OF OTHERS,
AND SOME LESSONS LEARNED.

01:14:49.167 --> 01:14:54.033
BUT DID YOU FIGURE OUT
THE HEAD FAKE?

01:14:54.033 --> 01:14:56.501
IT'S NOT ABOUT HOW
TO ACHIEVE YOUR DREAMS.

01:14:56.501 --> 01:14:59.234
IT'S ABOUT HOW
TO LEAD YOUR LIFE.

01:14:59.234 --> 01:15:00.968
IF YOU LEAD YOUR LIFE
THE RIGHT WAY,

01:15:00.968 --> 01:15:02.767
THE KARMA WILL TAKE CARE
OF ITSELF.

01:15:02.767 --> 01:15:05.534
THE DREAMS WILL COME TO YOU.

01:15:05.534 --> 01:15:10.767
HAVE YOU FIGURED OUT
THE SECOND HEAD FAKE?

01:15:10.767 --> 01:15:11.934
THE TALK'S NOT FOR YOU.

01:15:11.934 --> 01:15:13.033
IT'S FOR MY KIDS.

01:15:13.033 --> 01:15:15.601
THANK YOU ALL.
GOOD NIGHT.

01:15:15.601 --> 01:15:18.534
[applause]

